Value
Type: SystemDouble
The value of the considered overwrite item.
  1. Framing type
    • 0 = Program Default
    • 1 = SMF
    • 2 = IMF
    • 3 = OMF
    • 4 = SCBF
    • 5 = OCBF
    • 6 = OCBFI
    • 7 = EBF
    • 8 = BRBF
  2. Omega0

    Value >= 0; 0 means use a program determined value.

  1. BRB Beta Factor

    Value >= 0; 0 means use a program determined value.

  2. BRB BetaOmega Factor

    Value >= 0; 0 means use a program determined value.

  3. Perform RBS capacity design
    • 0 = Program Default
    • 1 = No
    • 2 = Yes
  4. Consider deflection
    • 0 = Program Default
    • 1 = No
    • 2 = Yes
  5. Deflection check type
    • 0 = Program Default
    • 1 = Ratio
    • 2 = Absolute
    • 3 = Both
  6. DL deflection limit, L/Value

    Value >= 0; 0 means no check for this item.

  7. SDL + LL deflection limit, L/Value

    Value >= 0; 0 means no check for this item.

  8. LL deflection limit, L/Value

    Value >= 0; 0 means no check for this item.

  9. Total load deflection limit, L/Value

    Value >= 0; 0 means no check for this item.

  10. Total load deflection minus camber limit, L/Value

    Value >= 0; 0 means no check for this item.

  11. DL deflection limit, absolute

    Value >= 0; 0 means no check for this item. [L]

  12. SDL + LL deflection limit, absolute

    Value >= 0; 0 means no check for this item. [L]

  13. LL deflection limit, absolute

    Value >= 0; 0 means no check for this item. [L]

  14. Total load deflection limit, absolute

    Value >= 0; 0 means no check for this item. [L]

  15. Total load deflection minus camber limit, absolute

    Value >= 0; 0 means no check for this item. [L]

  16. Specified camber

    Value >= 0. [L]

  17. Net area to total area ratio

    Value >= 0; 0 means use program default value.

  18. Live load reduction factor

    Value >= 0; 0 means use program determined value.

  24. Effective length factor, K2 Major

    Value >= 0; 0 means use program determined value.

  25. Effective length factor, K2 Minor

    Value >= 0; 0 means use program determined value.

  26. Effective length factor, K Lateral Torsional Buckling

ProgDet
Type: SystemBoolean
If this item is True, the specified value is program determined.

Return Value

Type: Int32
Returns zero if the item is successfully retrieved; otherwise it returns a nonzero value.
Remarks
Examples
VB
Copy
Public Sub Example()
   Dim SapModel As cSapModel
   Dim EtabsObject As cOAPI
   Dim ret As Integer = -1
   Dim Value As Double
   Dim ProgDet As Boolean

'create ETABS object
   Dim myHelper as cHelper = New Helper
   EtabsObject = myHelper.CreateObjectProgID("CSI.ETABS.API.ETABSObject")

'start ETABS application
  ret = EtabsObject.ApplicationStart()

'create SapModel object
   SapModel = EtabsObject.SapModel

'initialize model
   ret = SapModel.InitializeNewModel()

'create steel deck template model
   ret = SapModel.File.NewSteelDeck(4, 12, 12, 4, 4, 24, 24)

'set steel design code
   ret = SapModel.DesignSteel.SetCode("AISC 360-10")

'run analysis
   System.IO.Directory.CreateDirectory("c:\CSI_API_temp")
   ret = SapModel.File.Save("C:\CSI_API_temp\example.edb")
   ret = SapModel.Analyze.RunAnalysis

'start steel design
   ret = SapModel.DesignSteel.StartDesign

'get overwrite item
   ret = SapModel.DesignSteel.AISC360_10.GetOverwrite("8", 2, Value, ProgDet)

'close ETABS
   EtabsObject.ApplicationExit(False)

'clean up variables
   SapModel = Nothing
   EtabsObject = Nothing

End Sub
